results.wikipedia_summary: Campylorhynchus is a genus of wrens, which has at least thirteen described species. At 17‚Äì22¬†cm (6.8-8.7¬†in), these are the largest-bodied of wrens, including the largest species, the Giant Wren. Member species are found in South and Central America and in some cases, as far north as southwestern United States.
